issue.body:
Hello,

I have discovered that from some point in time, i dont remember exactly when, the Table/Column Renaming option has just silently stopped working

I have tried ALL the options until now and combination of:
- UseT4 / Not Use T4
- Use HandleBars / NotUse
- UseDatabaseNames / Not use them

0) I have scratched my head to make it work.
1) As you know from before i have forked your tool to my VS here and i am maintaining it locally for my personal use, by removing ALL the things that you work hard to maintain there. Literally i want ONLY RevEng, Not any CLI and stuff, and Always on SQL Server and Always on .NET8 for example. 

2) First suspicion that i had there was the file is not loaded correctly. And indeed it was not.
Issue found in CustomNameOptionsExtensions => customNamingOptions is null there and returned null
using ( var ms = new MemoryStream( Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes( File.ReadAllText( optionsCustomNamePath , Encoding.UTF8 ) ) ) ) {
	var ser = new DataContractJsonSerializer( typeof( List<Schema> ) );
	var customNamingOptions = ser.ReadObject( ms ) as List<Schema>;
	return new Tuple<List<Schema> , string>( customNamingOptions , optionsCustomNamePath );
}

If i replace it with plain Newtonsoft.Json it returns fine the deserialized content, as i debugged it and stepped through it.
var test = File.ReadAllText( optionsCustomNamePath , Encoding.UTF8 );
List<Schema> aResult = Newtonsoft.Json.JsonConvert.DeserializeObject<List<Schema>>( test );
return new Tuple<List<Schema> , string>( aResult , optionsCustomNamePath );

I dont know what to do further on as it seems it is NOT so easy to test the Reveng.Core because it is run by the console app ( thank you microsoft for your stupid ideas to remove totally support in VS for EF )

Thank you very much as always for your GREAT effort to maintain such a nice and useful tool

### Provide steps to reproduce a bug
Example of epft.renaming.json
[
    {
        "UseSchemaName": false,
        "SchemaName": "dbo",
        "Tables": [
            {
                "Name": "manufacturer",
                "NewName": "Mymanufacturer",
                "Columns": [
                    {
                        "Name": "Manufacturer",
                        "NewName": "ManufacturerName"
                    },
                    {
                        "Name": "Manufacturer1",
                        "NewName": "ManufacturerName"
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "Name": "MySP_Result",
                "NewName": "TestResult"
            }

        ]
    }
]

### Provide technical details

- EF Core Power Tools version: Latest

- Exact Visual Studio version: (e.g. Visual Studio 2022 17.8.3)

- Database engine: SQL Server

- EF Core version in use: (e.g. EF Core 8)

- Is Handlebars templates used: no

- Is T4 templates used: yes

- Is a SQL Server .dacpac used: no
